technologies.name: WordPress
technologies.description: WordPress is a free and open-source content management system written in PHP and paired with a MySQL or MariaDB database. Features include a plugin architecture and a template system.

technologies.name: MySQL
technologies.description: MySQL is an open-source relational database management system.

technologies.name: PHP
technologies.description: PHP is a general-purpose scripting language used for web development.

technologies.name: Chart.js
technologies.description: Chart.js is an open-source JavaScript library that allows you to draw different types of charts by using the HTML5 canvas element.

technologies.name: MediaElement.js
technologies.description: MediaElement.js is a set of custom Flash plugins that mimic the HTML5 MediaElement API for browsers that don't support HTML5 or don't support the media codecs.

technologies.name: Stripe
technologies.description: Stripe offers online payment processing for internet businesses as well as fraud prevention, invoicing and subscription management.

technologies.name: EmbedPlus
technologies.description: EmbedPlus is a WordPress plugin for YouTube allows you to embed gallery, channel, playlist, or even live stream on your webpage.

technologies.name: AddToAny Share Buttons
technologies.description: AddToAny Share Buttons plugin for WordPress increases traffic and engagement by helping people share your posts and pages to any service.

technologies.name: WooCommerce
technologies.description: WooCommerce is an open-source ecommerce plugin for WordPress.

technologies.name: WooCommerce Stripe Payment Gateway
technologies.description: WooCommerce Stripe Payment Gateway plugin extends WooCommerce allowing you to take payments directly on your store via Stripe’s API.

technologies.name: Divi
technologies.description: Divi is a WordPress Theme and standalone WordPress plugin from Elegant themes that allows users to build websites using the visual drag-and-drop Divi page builder.

technologies.name: jQuery Mobile
technologies.description: jQuery Mobile is a HTML5-based user interface system designed to make responsive web sites and apps that are accessible on all smartphone, tablet and desktop devices.

technologies.name: WooCommerce Multilingual
technologies.description: WooCommerce Multilingual plugin makes it possible to run fully multilingual ecommerce sites using WooCommerce and WPML.

technologies.name: WPML
technologies.description: WPML plugin makes it possible to build and run fully multilingual WordPress sites.

technologies.name: AddToAny
technologies.description: AddToAny is a universal sharing platform that can be integrated into a website by use of a web widget or plugin.

technologies.name: PhotoSwipe
technologies.description: PhotoSwipe is an open-source gallery to support JavaScript-based image zooming.

technologies.name: Moment.js
technologies.description: Moment.js is a free and open-source JavaScript library that removes the need to use the native JavaScript Date object directly.

technologies.name: Matomo Analytics
technologies.description: Matomo Analytics is a free and open-source web analytics application, that runs on a PHP/MySQL web-server.

technologies.name: Lodash
technologies.description: Lodash is a JavaScript library which provides utility functions for common programming tasks using the functional programming paradigm.

technologies.name: jQuery UI
technologies.description: jQuery UI is a collection of GUI widgets, animated visual effects, and themes implemented with jQuery, Cascading Style Sheets, and HTML.

technologies.name: jQuery Migrate
technologies.description: Query Migrate is a javascript library that allows you to preserve the compatibility of your jQuery code developed for versions of jQuery older than 1.9.

technologies.name: jQuery
technologies.description: jQuery is a JavaScript library which is a free, open-source software designed to simplify HTML DOM tree traversal and manipulation, as well as event handling, CSS animation, and Ajax.

technologies.name: Tippy.js
technologies.description: Tippy.js is the complete tooltip, popover, dropdown, and menu solution for the web, powered by Popper.

technologies.name: Priority Hints
technologies.description: Priority Hints exposes a mechanism for developers to signal a relative priority for browsers to consider when fetching resources.

technologies.name: Google Font API
technologies.description: Google Font API is a web service that supports open-source font files that can be used on your web designs.

technologies.name: OVHcloud
technologies.description: OVHcloud is a global, cloud provider delivering hosted private cloud, public cloud, and dedicated server solutions.

technologies.name: Microsoft 365
technologies.description: Microsoft 365 is a line of subscription services offered by Microsoft as part of the Microsoft Office product line.

technologies.name: Popper
technologies.description: Popper is a positioning engine, its purpose is to calculate the position of an element to make it possible to position it near a given reference element.

technologies.name: RSS
technologies.description: RSS is a family of web feed formats used to publish frequently updated works—such as blog entries, news headlines, audio, and video—in a standardized format.

technologies.name: Open Graph
technologies.description: Open Graph is a protocol that is used to integrate any web page into the social graph.
